    "summary": "A PhD in applied physics with 10+ years of experience in multidisciplinary R&D and systems engineering. Broad expertise in physics: ranging from optics (nano-scale microscopy, image formation, and (bio)sensors) to materials science (microtechnology, surface chemistry, and electron coherence). Strong in technology evolution by (statistical) mathematical modelling, experimentation, and image/signal analysis. \nWith my strong sense of responsibility to deliver value, I keep focus on the objective and provide structure and prioritization. I have an open way of communicating and reporting, and enjoy to bring constructive discussions and enthusiasm to project teams. Having the opportunity to learn and explore on the front-end of knowledge makes me most effective and energetic.\n\nTechnical knowledge:\n\u2022 Data and image processing / visualization\n\u2022 Microscopy: (single molecule) fluorescence optical microscopy, (functional) AFM, TEM\n\u2022 Optics / bench optomechanics / image theory / metrology\n\u2022 Microtechnology / Lithography / Thin Films / Superconductivity / Microfluidics / Lab-on-a-chip\n\u2022 Statistical modelling (PhD) / statistical analysis (Six Sigma Black Belt)\n\u2022 Solid state physics / Surface physics\n\u2022 Protein dynamics and interactions (molecular biophysics) \n\nProgramming languages: \n\u2022 MatLAB (expert)\n\u2022 Python\n\u2022 JAVA (Android)\n\u2022 data and image processing techniques (computer vision)\n\nTechnical software: \n\u2022 TIBCO Spotfire (large dataset visualization)\n\u2022 Minitab\n\u2022 Enterprise Architect / Capella (SysML)\n\nSkills / Certifications: \n\u2022 Academic & Industrial Research\n\u2022 Product development and innovation\n\u2022 System engineering (architecture, integration)\n\u2022 Project management (PRINCE2 Foundation certified)\n\u2022 Six Sigma Black Belt\n\nBesides work I enjoy to do rock climbing, and to care for my daughters.",
